EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By the Chair of the Land Use Committee Council Member Comrie
Pursuant to Rule 11.20(c) of the Council and Section 197-d(b)(3) of the New York City Charter, the Council hereby resolves that the action of the City Planning Commission on Uniform Land Use Procedure Application no. C 100156 ZSK, a special permit, shall be subject to Council review.  This application is related to application no. C 100155 HAK that is subject to Council review pursuant to Section 197-d of the New York City Charter.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to make nurses available to public and private primary and intermediate schools with at least one hundred students.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to make nurses available to public and private primary and intermediate schools with at least one hundred students.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of aerosol spray paint cans and broad tipped indelible markers.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of aerosol spray paint cans and broad tipped indelible markers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to accepting legally blind applicants for New York city disability parking permits.
EventItemMatterName: Accepting legally blind applicants for New York City Disability Parking Permits.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the conversion of residential buildings to other usage.
EventItemMatterName: Conversion of residential buildings to other usage.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to improving the health and safety of nail salon employees.
EventItemMatterName: Improving the health and safety of nail salon employees.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter in relation to extending the time limits during July and August for community board action with respect to the uniform land use review procedure.
EventItemMatterName: ULURP, Community Board Action Time Limits

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Department of State to promulgate standards and rules concerning the sanitization of mattresses that include requirements sufficient to eradicate bedbugs in reconditioned mattresses before their sale.
EventItemMatterName: Promulgate standards and rules concerning the sanitization of mattresses that include requirements sufficient to eradicate bedbugs in reconditioned mattresses before their sale.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of tickets to the general public by operators of theater, music, or sporting events taking place in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of tickets to the general public by operators of theater, music, or sporting events taking place in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution commemorating the life and legacy of legendary entertainer and civil rights activist, Lena Horne.
EventItemMatterName: Commemorating the life and legacy of legendary entertainer and civil rights activist, Lena Horne.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Community Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to enact H.R.3734, the “Urban Revitalization and Livable Communities Act,” which would authorize the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development to establish and carry out an urban revitalization and livable communities program to provide federal grants to urban areas for the rehabilitation of critically needed recreational areas and facilities and development of improved recreation programs, and for other purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to enact H.R.3734, the “Urban Revitalization and Livable Communities Act.”

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing reporting requirements for the department of citywide administrative services on the status of city-owned real property
EventItemMatterName: Establishing reporting requirements for the department of citywide administrative services on the status of city-owned real property.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of pending legislation in the New York State Legislature intended to strengthen regulations governing the sale and licensing of firearms.
EventItemMatterName: Strengthen regulations governing the sale and licensing of firearms.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the creation of a task force on stepstreets.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a task force on stepstreets.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to raising the sales age from eighteen to twenty-one years for cigarettes and tobacco products and establishing a sales age of twenty-one years for electronic cigarettes.
EventItemMatterName: Raising the legal tobacco products sales age to twenty-one years.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the payment of a living wage to employees employed on property developed by recipients of financial assistance for economic development.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the payment of a living wage to employees employed on property developed by recipients of financial assistance for economic development.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the City from unnecessarily purchasing bottled water.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the City from unnecessarily purchasing bottled water.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the New York City Police Department to report on complaints of harassment in the transit system.
EventItemMatterName: NYPD to report on complaints of harassment in the transit system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to reconcile and pass A.10163 and S.8380 and the Governor to sign into law, an act to amend the Labor Law in relation to establishing the Wage Theft Prevention Act.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing the Wage Theft Prevention Act. (A.10163/S.8380)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2010 Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2010 Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to unlawful sidewalk ATMs.
EventItemMatterName: Regulating sidewalk ATMs as revocable consents and requiring safety features for all outdoor ATMs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to the annual report required by certain entities which enter into contracts with the department of small business services.
EventItemMatterName: Annual report required by certain entities which enter into contracts with the department of small business services.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Community Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to amend the Community Reinvestment Act to provide credits to financial institutions that fund affordable middle-income housing construction projects that have stalled or suspended their activities due to a discontinuance of project funding.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to amend the Community Reinvestment Act.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the creation of a Street Vendor Advisory Board.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a Street Vendor Advisory Board.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution to amend the text of the New York City Zoning Resolution to require a Special Permit to be granted by the City Planning Commission for the installation of telephone exchanges or communications equipment in Residence Districts.
EventItemMatterName: Installation of telephone exchanges or communications equipment in Residence Districts.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of Education (DOE) to institute a policy that would limit the aggregate amount of homework that is given to elementary and middle grade school children to approximately ten minutes per grade level on any given night, and would include a homework-free night to allow children to participate in other activities, exercise and spend quality time with their families.
EventItemMatterName: Dep't of Education to institute a policy that would limit the aggregate amount of homework that is given to elementary and middle grade school children to approximately ten minutes per grade level on any given night.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of pending legislation in the New York State Legislature intended to amend the penal law in relation to the offense of non-support of a child.
EventItemMatterName: Offense of non-support of a child.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to limiting the time period for parking at parking meters.
EventItemMatterName: Limiting the time period for parking at parking meters.
